Module mesakit.graph.core

Class Metadata

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.mesakit.graph.Metadata
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, com.telenav.kivakit.core.string.AsIndentedString, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Named, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.Stringable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.StringSource, com.telenav.kivakit.validation.Validatable
public class Metadata extends Object implements com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Named, com.telenav.kivakit.core.string.AsIndentedString, com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, com.telenav.kivakit.validation.Validatable
Information about map data in a resource like a file.

Metadata in a Resource containing map data, can be extracted with from(File). The structure of metadata in a PBF resource is described in the link above. Partial metadata can be obtained from a metadata descriptor with parseDescriptor(String) and the descriptor for a Metadata object can be retrieved with descriptor().

Three categories of metadata are available:

Data Description

  • name()
  • dataSpecification()
  • dataBounds()
  • dataBuild()
  • dataFormat()
  • dataPrecision()
  • dataSize()
  • dataSupplier()
  • dataVersion()
  • descriptor()

Source Data Statistics

  • nodeCount(CountType)
  • wayCount(CountType)
  • relationCount(CountType)

Graph Information

  • vertexCount(CountType)
  • edgeCount(CountType)
  • forwardEdgeCount(CountType)
  • edgeRelationCount(CountType)
  • placeCount(CountType)
  • shapePointCount(CountType)
  • graphElementCount(CountType)

Metadata objects are KryoSerializable and implement Stringable. They are also Validatable and can be validated with the Validator returned by validator(ValidationType). If no validation of statistics is desired the ValidationType VALIDATE_EXCEPT_STATISTICS can be passed as the validation type. For convenience, full validation can be performed with Validatable.isValid(Listener).

jonathanl (shibo)

    • parse

      public static Metadata parse(String value)
      Parses a complete standardized metadata string of the form:
      • [data-supplier]-[data-specification]-[data-format]-[name]-[bounds]?-[data-version]?-[data-build]?.
      • HERE-UniDb-PBF-North_America-2007Q4-2020.04.01_04.01PM_PT
      • OSM-OSM-PBF-Seattle-47.5840818_-122.2169381_47.6419581_-122.1590618
      The data version and build are optional.
